FBIS3-61034 "jpuma002___94012" JPRS-UMA-94-002 Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Central Eurasia Military Affairs 5 January 1994 STATE AND LOCAL MILITARY FORCES UKRAINE Radetskiy on Changing Stance Toward CIS Joint Forces LD2212120493 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1130 GMT 22 Dec 93 LD2212120493 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [By ITAR-TASS special correspondent Vladimir Gondusov] [Text] Ashgabat, 22 December -- Ukraine will be taking the most active part in the work of the CIS Council of Defense Ministers, and is pursuing the goal of having its permanent representatives at the headquarters of the CIS Joint Armed Forces. This was stated today by General of the Army Vitaliy Radetskiy, the Ukrainian Defense Minister, at a session of the heads of military departments of the Commonwealth countries in Ashgabat. He noted that the republic's leadership has reconsidered its attitude toward the CIS coordinating military bodies in which it was not participating earlier. Ukraine is interested in cooperation with these military bodies.
